	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9766856055728>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Best Warrior Race Out There</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Dec 13th 5:33 AM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=8127><span id= >Praxxis</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If you want to play a warrior, go for the Iksar. Reasons:<br><br>1) High agility, and Swimming at 100 to begin with.<br><br>2) Forage, a very useful skill.<br><br>3) Beginning Iksar warriors get a pike that usually hits for about 12-16 damage...and that's starting off!<br><br>4) Doing the quest for Curscale Armor for Klok Mugruk not only gets you a full set of not bad armor for early levels, but also gets you to level 5 before you know it.<br><br>I've only played one warrior, and it's Iksar, and if given the chance, I don't think I'd want to play any other race. They are the best, without a doubt. There is that whole pesky KoS to everything problem, but there's nothing you need that you can't find in Kunark. If you wanted, you could easily reach lvl 30 and never step foot off the continent. Sure, it would be dull, but you take what you can get. Well, there's my 2cp, now let's get on with the bashing of my comment!!!</p>&nbsp;<br>Praxxis<br>Warrior and Officer of<br>The Knights Discordia<br></td></td></tr>
