	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'd have to Agree with Zubekhan here; to a point.<br><br>Ogres are awesome Warriors... the ability to not be stunned from the front really helps this race alot, making them shine compared to other warriors.<br><br>One thing niether of you mentioned was the Iksar's innate AC bonus... they increase AC at an incredible rate.<br><br>Personally, I think AC is a Warrior's most important stat... we are the "tanks" of a group. Our job is not to do damage, but to take it. So many Warriors get upset at our damage dealing; nothing compared to punt casters... But that is the point. Casters are the damage dealers of EQ. Warriors are the Bodyguards of EQ.<br><br>Its that simple. We keep the group alive just like a Cleric does, except we take damage instead of heal it.<br><br>That said, my main warrior is an Ogre, but I have recently started an Iksar warrior and have to say they are truly enjoyable. In the beginning years, its so easy to find a group and get started its almost laughable.<br><br>There are so few warriors in Cabilis (everyone jumps on the monk/necro bandwagon..) that it is simple to adventure with a partner. AC wise, I think I gain about 4 points of AC for every 1 point I done... nice.<br><br>And don't get me started on the Iksar Monk AC bonus... insane.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
